<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Seattle, Washington 1/26/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.94)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2134'>Keith "Gen" Watabayashi</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=2134&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 27, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Greetings from Seattle. After playing in Star Wars/Star Trek tournaments for the last 3 years, this was to be my first LOTR tourney. With School and everything I haven&#39;t been able to make it to one before, so I was looking foward to playing.  My playtest buddies (Jack +Cameron) were apparently busy so they couldn&#39;t make it today, but they helped me with my decks a little, and props to Cameron for lending me some cards.<br>
For this tourney I took my Ranger deck (&quot;Iron and Steel&quot; on my page), with a Sauron Direct Damage deck. This tournament was held at Booster Pack Gaming (formerly Broken Games), had about 25 people give or take a few, and would last 5 games.<br>
<br>
**sidenote** When I got to Booster Pack, I was surprised to see many old Star Wars players there, and not just any players, but some very notable ones like Derek Snook, Peter Sundholm, and Charles Hickey. It was great to see guys again, and hopefully this game will be a new chance to compete with them for another 3 years.<br>
<br>
Game 1; V.S. Derek Snook starting Arwen+Legolas<br>
<br>
I bid 1, he bids 3 and goes first. Surprise surprise he starts the Pony, and our decks look like mirror images (I also start Arwen/Legolas/Pony). My hand doesn&#39;t have much, 1 Bowmen, a couple Orcs, he makes it to my site 2 , and decides to stay there. I get Aragorn, play a No Stranger, a Ranger Sword, and start moving. Snook also doesn&#39;t have much in the way of minions, I think all he played was an Orc Ambusher and a Under the Watching Eye, so that wasn&#39;t a big deal. What was a big deal, was when I moved to Site 3, and Snook busts out The Ford. Hmmm. Out comes Attea and 2 more UTWE . WTF? Oh well. I survive though, and am at Site 3, one ahead of Snook. Next turn I still can&#39;t do much, so he makes it to Site 3, and lets his shadow go to work. After I totally heal my party (5 wounds from Sanc., Aragorn&#39;s text, Aragorn from hand), I move to the Chamber, and have to exert THREE companions! Stupid Eyes, oh well. He plays a dude or two, then an Orc Bowmen, but I easiliy get through to and am at site 4. Snook heals, then moves to site 4, no big opposition from me, just some archers and whatnot. By now Snook has Aragorn&#39;s Bow, and the archery battle is outrageous, with him exerting guys left and right for pings, and me playing Goblin Marksman and Bowmen. Still, Snook can handle it pretty easily, and survives to 4, then double-steps to the Bridge...and I can&#39;t stop him. So, by now, Snook has out 3 Under the Watching Eyes, an Orc Bowmen, is ahead of me, and I have to move to the Bridge next turn. Suck. Well, on my turn, I Athelas a couple of wounds, and get ready for Khazad-Dum. I move, exert THREE guys, and Snook plays another Bowmen and 2 fierce Nazgul. Utilizing Gwemegil&#39;s text, Arwen&#39;s fate, and Swordsman of the N. Tower, I am able to survive attack, and even kill off one of the Nazgul. Still, I know I have put some kind of pressure on Snook, and get gutsy, and move again to site 6, which is his Galadriel&#39;s Glade. I exert Frodo a bunch (Isildur&#39;s Bane...so good), suck up 2 archery after he plays an Orc Scouting Band, fend off Cantea I think, and make to site 6, one ahead of Snook! Here is where I make a crucial decision, I need to draw some shadow to keep my lead, and my hand has been clogged with a Blade of Gondor and A Ranger&#39;s Versatility, so when it comes to decide what to dump for a card draw, I dump the Versatility. Snook&#39;s next turn, he just moves to site 6, I play another Bowmen, and since most of his party is wounded/exhausted, he stays at 6. My turn, I heal all but like one wound from Aragorn, and move to 7. No big resistance, he didn&#39;t have much, and I decide to stay. Snook just heals and move, wanting to kill me with his shadow no doubt.  Well, I play Boromir and his Blade move to 8 and am staring down The Witch King and Cantea, plus an Orc. Well, I&#39;m not too worried, give Cantea to Aragorn (who has a Last Alliance), and &quot;The King&quot; to Arwen. I do Arwen first, play an Arwen&#39;s Fate, 2 Swordmans, which equals the strength 16 king, then discard 2  cards from hand, and deal him to damage! Aragorn also beats Cantea when I play my 4th Swordsman, and if I kept my Verstality I could have played it, and killed both of them. But, I didn&#39;t, their fierce, and I take some wounds. I try to move again (jank Shadow in hand), out comes Tol Brandir, 3 Trackers, another Bowmen, and after Boromir + Legolas die to Archery, Frodo is overwhelmed...I lose.<br>
Full Loss<br>
1 Victory Point<br>
Total: +1<br>
<br>
Highs: A great game played against a great opponent.<br>
Lows: A long, long, long game.<br>
<br>
Game 2; V.S. Some little kid starting Merry+Pippin+Sam<br>
<br>
I bid 1, he bids 0, I go first. My hand is awesome, 5 Shadow cards (two Bowmen) and 3 good fellowship cards, and so I get Aragorn, play Bow of the Galadrhim move to his Site 2 (Buckleberry Ferry), and he plays a Goblin Scavengers and a Runner, and Bow of the Galadrhim kills them both! I make to 3 easily, and let him go. He doesn&#39;t play much, a Bounder or two, and gets to 3 with no problem. I heal, move to 4, then make the dumbest mistake of my LOTR career, and double-move to site 5, against Moria....hmm. Well, Keyward, Runner, Cave Troll and Hammer. Hmm. Arwen dies, then Legolas dies. Hmmm. His next turn I play as much as can, hoping I can draw a Boromir or Sam, I don&#39;t. I move to Dimrall Dale next turn with just Aragorn and Frodo, 5 minions, game over. <br>
Full Loss<br>
Victory Poins: 1<br>
Total: +2<br>
<br>
Highs: Uhhh...<br>
Lows: Damage +2, power 18 Troll....<br>
<br>
Game 3; V.S. Narayan starting Gimli+Arwen<br>
<br>
This game was fast, I went second, and after he moved to my site three (Rivendell Waterfall), I triple move next turn to his Site 4, Pass of Caradhras. Narayan is playing pretty much the same shadow as Snook, lots of Sauron direct damage, (like me) but unlike Snook, he does not have out uber-Under the Watching Eyes, and am double-stepping almost every turn. However, at site 6, when Narayan wants to double-move to 7 and pass me, he exerts Gimli during Manuveur phase with Shoulder to Shoulder, I &#39;Hate&#39; him before he can use Shoulder to Shoulder to heal him. (hehe). At Any rate, with Gimli gone Narayan has to go one at a time, so he relies on his shadow at sites 8-9 to get the job done. Unfortunately for him, I have the Versatilitys and Events to kill easiy kill off his minions, and even with Tol Brandir, I make to site 9 with little resistance.<br>
Full Win<br>
Victory Points: 3<br>
Total: +5<br>
<br>
Highs: Winning and &#39;hating&#39; Gimli.<br>
Lows: Quick game with little excitement.<br>
<br>
Game 4; V.S. Nick H. starting Legolas+Arwen<br>
<br>
Nick has always owned me with his Moria in fun games, but today, at this tourney, I felt good about my chances. I go first, and it turns out that Nick is no playing Moria today, but Nazgul.  I am facing down The Witch King at site 2, which sucks, but I survive the attack  with Arwen and Aragorn taking the hits. Then, much to Nick&#39;s surprise, I move again to the Ford of Bruinen. Nick plays Enquea for 1, then uses the remaing 8 (some leftover) and plays Nelya via Gates, then Cantea. Thinking he has me, I remind him that the Ford is a river, and exhaust Witch King and Enquea, then Legolas kills them both. Aragorn and Arwen deal with the remaining guys, and I am safely at site 3. Nick&#39;s turn, he plays an ASSLOAD of archery (Elven Bow on Arwen, Aragorn&#39;s Bow, Splendor,), and moves. I am lucky with 2 Bowmen in my and, and just play them. Nick moves to 3 with no problems, and it&#39;s my go. I move oto 4, face a couple Nazgul and some Goblin Runners, but am fine and stop at 4. Nick plays more archery (Orophin, Rumil) and moves to 4, takes some Archery and my third Bowmen comes out, then passes me and moves to site 5. I can&#39;t really stop him, so he is now ahead me, but his party is getting pretty wounded. I  add Boromir and his Blade to the party, move to site 5, encounter Attea and someone else, make short work of them (Arwen&#39;s Fate: good.) Then pass Nick and move to site 6 with no real problems. This was huge, since now that I am ahead, Nick will have to double-move twice if he wants to stop me, and that is what he does. He moves to 7, no takes some archery and Mordor Hate, but is alive and well (since at 6 all his allies took the hits). I double-move next turn, am ahead at site 8, and now Nick must double move or lose. He does, and moves to 8. Some Archery, some direct damage, still in pretty good shape, but Haldir and Frodo are exhausted, and Frodo has 8 burdens due to Isildur&#39;s Bane. Still, Nick knows he must move again, and I bring out Tol Brandir. Two Orcs, Three Orc Scouting Bands, and my 4th Orc Bowmen. Nick does the math, shoots this guy, wounds that guy, and after all archery is done, I have an un-hurt Orc Soldier and a wounded Orc Scouting Band facing down Aragorn and Frodo, who is only strength 4. Nick puts the Soldier on Frodo, I exert to Wound, and it&#39;s either give Frodo 5 wounds (he dies) or give Frodo Ten burdens (he&#39;s corrupted).<br>
Full Win<br>
Victory Points: 3<br>
Total: +8<br>
<br>
Highs: Playing Nick, he&#39;s a cool guy.<br>
Lows: Archery = Dagobah turtle<br>
<br>
Game 5; V.S. Nick O. starting Legolas+Arwen<br>
This kid looked to be about 10, but after what happened with the Cave Troll, I wasn&#39;t to under-estimate him. Well, I went second and drew pretty much all shadow. So, my strategy became to just go one site at a time an let the Shadow go to work. It did, and even though he had Aragorn&#39;s Bow, Legolas, and Sting, he was having a hard time dealing with all my direct damage. Still, by the time I was at site 5, he was at site 7, that&#39;s how fast he was going, and how slow I was going. (He was playing Uruk-Hai, so I was wary). However, at site 8, after I played about 3 orcs (including a Morgul Hunter) he didnn&#39;t have any Versatilitys, and after 2 Hates, goodbye Legolas, goodbye Arwen. After those two Hates he doesn&#39;t have an answer, and Frodo is overwhelmed at site 9.<br>
Full Win<br>
Victory Points:3<br>
Total: +11<br>
<br>
Final Score: 11 <br>
<br>
After all was said and done, I came in 7th out of 25, not to bad for my first tourney I guess. Peter Sundholm won the thing, going 5-0 and playing rangers/gandalf with Nazgul swarm (Morgul gates, cheap Nazgul). Derek Snook took second, losing only to Peter, and I believe John Runningdeer took 3rd, and Charles Hickey got 4th. All the former Star Wars players took top honors (except for me, cause I suck :) ). Cool.<br>
Overall a fun time and I look foward to my next chance at killing Frodo!<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
<br>
None, because I hate doing them!<br>
<br>
Slops:<br>
<br>
Anyone who rates me down for writing props/slops.<br>
<br>
Later all,<br>
